Interface JumpNever

All Known Implementing Classes:

public interface JumpNever

Interface that is to be implemented by any instruction that will never lead to a jump in the control flow. If this interface is implemented, the interfaces JumpAlways, JumpConditional, JumpInvocation, JumpException and JumpSwitching must not be implemented.

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-03-10
Author:
Tim Majchrzak
